#Getting Started with Git + GitHub

1. Sign up with github.com/join
2. Create a new repository (repo)
3. Download and install git-scm.com/downloads
4. Open Git Bash app (Windows)
5. Move to your desktop by entering: cd ~/desktop in the command line
6. Enter: git config --global user.name "Your Name"
7. Enter: git config --global user.email "Email"
8. Enter: git init engl507test (create directory)
9. Enter: git cd engl507test (create directory)
10. Enter: touch index.md (create file)
11. Enter: open index.md (open file)
12. In the file, write a few words using the Markdown syntax
13. Save your file: ctrl + S
14. In the command line, enter: git remote add origin http://github.com/handle/repo.git
**Replace handle with your GitHub handle and repo with your repo name. Keep .git at the end**
15. Enter: git remote -v (verify)
16. Enter: git add --all (add changes)
17. Enter: git commit -m "message" (record and describe changes)
18. Enter: git push origin master (push changes to your repo)
19. Repeat
